# Core Data Structures

The foundational types for intentc. This module has zero dependencies on other intentc packages. All types are serializable to JSON and YAML.

## Intent

A parsed .ic file.

- `Name` (string) - Feature identifier, matches directory path.
- `Version` (integer) - Schema version.
- `DependsOn` (list of strings) - Dependency names.
- `Tags` (list of strings) - Categorization tags.
- `Profile` (string, optional) - Named agent profile for this target.
- `Content` (string) - Raw markdown body.
- `FilePath` (string) - Absolute path to source file.

## ValidationFile

A parsed .icv file containing multiple validations.

- `Target` (string) - Feature this validates.
- `Version` (integer) - Schema version.
- `JudgeProfile` (string, optional) - Agent profile for llm_judge evaluations.
- `Validations` (list of Validation) - The validation entries.
- `FilePath` (string) - Absolute path to source file.

## Validation

A single validation entry from an .icv file.

- `Name` (string) - Unique identifier.
- `Type` (ValidationType) - One of: `file_check`, `folder_check`, `command_check`, `llm_judge`.
- `Hidden` (boolean) - If true, the agent doesn't see this during generation.
- `Parameters` (map) - Type-specific parameters.

## Target

A buildable unit: an intent paired with its validations and resolved dependencies.

- `Name` (string) - Feature identifier.
- `Intent` (Intent) - The parsed intent.
- `Validations` (list of ValidationFile) - Associated validation files.
- `Dependencies` (list of Target) - Resolved dependency targets.
- `Status` (TargetStatus) - One of: `pending`, `building`, `built`, `failed`, `outdated`.

## SchemaViolation

A schema validation error or warning.

- `FilePath` (string) - File with the violation.
- `Field` (string) - Field that failed.
- `Message` (string) - Human-readable description.
- `Severity` (string) - `error` or `warning`.

## BuildResult

Outcome of building a single target.

- `Target` (string) - Target name.
- `GenerationID` (string) - Unique build identifier (e.g., `gen-1234567890`).
- `Success` (boolean) - Whether the build succeeded.
- `Error` (string) - Error message if failed.
- `GeneratedAt` (timestamp) - When the build completed.
- `Files` (list of strings) - Files created or modified.
- `OutputDir` (string) - Output directory used.
- `Steps` (list of BuildStep) - Ordered build steps. Defaults to empty list.
- `TotalDurationSeconds` (float) - Wall-clock build time. Defaults to 0.

## BuildStep

One discrete phase of a build, with timing.

- `Phase` (BuildPhase) - One of: `resolve_deps`, `read_plan`, `build`, `post_build`, `validate`.
- `Status` (StepStatus) - One of: `success`, `failed`, `skipped`.
- `StartedAt` (timestamp)
- `EndedAt` (timestamp)
- `DurationSeconds` (float)
- `Summary` (string) - Brief human-readable description.
- `Error` (string) - Error message if failed, empty on success.
- `FilesChanged` (int) - Number of files affected.
- `DiffStat` (string) - e.g., "3 files changed, +45 -12".
- `Diff` (string) - Full unified diff, populated on post_build.

## ValidationResult

Outcome of running a single validation.

- `ValidationName` (string) - Which validation was run.
- `Passed` (boolean)
- `Message` (string) - Human-readable result.
- `Details` (list of strings) - Additional detail lines.
- `Severity` (string) - `error` or `warning`.
